**Summary:** Yājñavalkya Smṛti ch. 2 addresses false witnesses at Yj_2.81–2.83. The core ruling (Yj_2.81) prescribes a fine of **double the amount in dispute** for false witnesses, with **banishment** for Brāhmaṇas instead. A witness who later recants his own testimony (Yj_2.82) faces a heavier fine of **eight times** the amount (or banishment if Brāhmaṇa). Yj_2.83 carves out an exception when true testimony would cause someone's death, requiring the twice-born offender to offer a porridge sacrifice to Sarasvatī for purification.
